title: Alphabet Inc. Outperforms S&P 500 — TradingView News
text: Alphabet Inc. (GOOG) has seen a positive adjustment in its latest trading sessions, ending at $142.56 and $140.95 respectively. This performance outpaced the S&P 500's loss. Over the past month, Alphabet's stock has climbed by 4.33% and 4.16%, exceeding the sector's gain. The financial results of Alphabet Inc. are eagerly anticipated. The company is expected to post an EPS of $1.62, up 54.29% from the prior-year quarter. The projected net sales are $70.59 billion, up 11.83% from the year-ago period. In terms of valuation, Alphabet holds a Forward P/E ratio of 20.59, marking a discount compared to its industry's average Forward P/E of 23.86. The company currently has a PEG ratio of 1.24, compared to its industry's average PEG ratio of 1.99. For the current quarter, Alphabet Inc. is expected to post earnings of $1.62 per share, indicating a change of +54.3% from the year-ago quarter. The consensus earnings estimate for the current fiscal year is $5.83, pointing to a change of +27.9% from the prior year. For the next fiscal year, the consensus earnings estimate of $6.74 indicates a change of +15.6% from the previous year. The consensus sales estimate of $70.59 billion for the current quarter points to a year-over-year change of +11.8%. The estimates for the current and next fiscal years are $254.75 billion and $284.03 billion, indicating changes of +8.9% and +11.5%, respectively. Traders and investors use our platform.
